# BPI-R2-OPENWRT-18.06

Supports BananaPi BPI-R2

1. Pre-Install Toolsï¼š
```
apt-get install subversion build-essential libncurses5-dev zlib1g-dev gawk git ccache gettext libssl-dev xsltproc unzip subversion file
```

2. Check out code to openwrt18.06
'''
check to openwrt-18.06: git checkout -b openwrt-18.06 remotes/origin/openwrt-18.06

'''

3. Get latest packages which are defined in feeds.conf
```
./scripts/feeds update -a
./scripts/feeds install -a
```

4. Run "make menuconfig" to config your image
'''
Target System (MediaTek Ralink ARM)                                                                                                     
Subtarget (MT7623)                                                                                                                       
Target Profile (MTK7623n BananaPi R2)    
'''

5. Run "export FORCE_UNSAFE_CONFIGURE=1"

6. Run "make -j1 V=s" commmand to build code

7. After built, the SD image(mtk-bpi-r2-SD.img) and EMMC image(mtk-bpi-r2-EMMC.img) will be created in here: 

build_dir/target-arm_cortex-a7+neon-vfpv4_musl_eabi/linux-mediatek_mt7623/

